snippet.textDisplay: Having met her in person several times, I can say 100% she is as lovely, kind and inclusive in person as she is on screen. She is one of the few celebrities that you feel comfortable talking to as a friend and she will follow up with you afterwards if you needed support - something very few, if any, celebrities do. She supports so many minority causes IN ACTION by directly participating in events and donating  - Black Lives Matter, Save the Children, LGBT, Dreamers. Haters will always hate, but those who had the fortune to know her for years both as an artist and as a human - in person - will always look at her as a role model & love her for the beautiful soul she is. Her personality shines through in this interview. Her soul is buried in her music, so if you want to know her better, stream her album Romance. 💕💕💕
